Name:	 lxc-provider
Date:    Jan 2 2010
Version: 0.2 (alpha stage)
License:	LGPL as lxc-debian from original lxc package
Description :
	This suite of scripts and configuration files helps you make "ready to run" containers.

How it works :
	Deployement of new container is done in 2 steps :
	- create a cache for the targeted distribution
	- create the container

Install :
	I use /lxc to store containers and lxc-provider
	If you want to use another location modify (one line each) :
	./lxc/bin/lxc-provider
	./lxc/bin/lxc-template
	./lxc/etc/lxc-provider.conf 
	to reflect the new location

	I will suppose you use /lxc too:
	
	tar xvzf lxc-provider -C /
	export PATH="${PATH}:/lxc/bin"

Usage :
	To install an ubuntu karmic :
	- Change network settings in /lxc/etc/provisionning/net.conf
	- Make sure your ethernet bridge is up
		brctl addbr br0
	- Let's make a distrib cache 
		# lxc-template create debian/ubuntu/karmic
	- if there is no problem, make the container
		# lxc-provider create debian/ubuntu/karmic  -i 10.0.0.100 -n mycontainer
	- start the container
		# lxc-start -n mycontainer	
	- wait a minute (first karmic start is slow)
	- ssh 10.0.0.100
	- enjoy :)

